The paper discusses distributed virtual machine consolidation in cloud data centers, which involves resource allocation and optimization. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The paper also involves network infrastructure (NI) and system engineering (SY) aspects. Additionally, it discusses simulation experiments (SE) and performance evaluation (PF) of the proposed approaches.
